messages.message:
Nationwide has inquired about the following topics/questions as they are evaluating potentially using their own Azure OpenAI endpoint. Can someone please assist with these? We need the answers prior to our session with Nationwide on Wednesday. Thank you in advance! cc @Dale DeLoy @hannah

• Expected # of Requests/Prompts per Minute (Anticipated load on the API) –
• Expected Prompt Tokens per Request (Average number of tokens per prompt request)
• Expected Completion Tokens per Request (Average number of tokens for the completion of the request)

the answer to the first bullet depends on the expected load on AI Hub

for the other ones, i guess we can try to answer based on the OpenAI rate limits we set - @Aaron Tami can you help with this?
Nationwide is a top deal for us, so critical for us to get answers for them. Here is the email direct from the customer for additional context:
@Kerry this is what we discussed in our sync this week. We need numbers like this from our model dev team in order to properly provision our azure resources
